The paper deals with the problem of rendezvous in networks, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. The paper presents algorithms for this problem and analyzes the tradeoffs between time and cost. This makes it likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The problem also involves communication and networking, which makes it relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The algorithms presented in the paper involve data structures and algorithms, which makes it relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also involves analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which makes it relevant to the Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of rendezvous in a synchronous setting, which makes it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
